# simple web infrastructure design (using whiteboard):
https://imgur.com/g3Pnuaf

# What is a server?
A device responsible for hosting and serving the web app, in our case it has an IP addr 8.8.8.8 and a port 80

# What is the role of domain name?
website address on the internet in ourcase we using (www.foobar.com)

# What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com?
The A record for domain name mapped to the server's IP address.

# What is the role of the web server?
Handles incoming HTTP reqs to the app server.

# What is the role of the application server?
code execution, req processing and database interactions.

# What is the role of the database?
Storing and managing data.

# What does "SPOF" stands for?
Single Point Of Failure

Issues:
SPOF: If the server goes down, website will go down as well.
Downtime During Maintenance (DDM): To update the website we need to take down the system temporarily.
Limited Scalability: If website gets too much traffic, with a single server it won't be able to handle that much inc traffic.
